carpet.rule.commandItemShadowing.desc: Enable /itemshadowing command to create a shadow of the item in the main hand
carpet.rule.bindingCurseInvalidation.des: Enable player to take off armors with binding curse enchantments
Disable detection of open water in fishing, thus allowing fishing for treasures in any water
carpet.rule.creativeImmuneKill.desc: When enabled, this will prevent the /kill command from targeting players in Creative Mode or Spectator Mode
carpet.rule.staringEndermanNotAngry.desc: Disable enderman getting angry when player stares at them
carpet.rule.maxBlockPlaceDistance.desc: Set the maximum block placement distance
Also works for blocks breaking and interaction
carpet.rule.simpleUpdateSkipper.desc: Backport update skipper before 1.20-pre2 by disconnecting the redstone wire and prevent comparator dropping over tripdoors
carpet.rule.channelingIgnoreWeather.desc: Ignore the weather condition when using channeling enchantment
carpet.rule.notDamageEnderPearl.desc: Disable the falling damage when using ender pearl
carpet.rule.disableDamageImmunity.desc: Disable the immunity after sustaining damage
carpet.rule.turtleEggFastHatch.desc: Make turtle eggs always crack when random ticked, rather than cracking with a 1/500 chance
carpet.rule.openShulkerBoxForcibly.desc: Allow players to open the shulker box forcibly, even for those boxes blocked by a solid blocks
carpet.rule.fireworkRocketUseCooldown.de: Add a cooldown for using firework rocket
carpet.rule.riptideIgnoreWeather.desc: Ignore the weather condition when using riptide enchantment
carpet.rule.villagerHeal.desc: Heal villagers for 1 health every 4 seconds
carpet.rule.fakePlayerHeal.desc: Heal fake players for 1 health every 2 seconds
carpet.rule.knockbackStick.desc: Enable knockback stick, i.e. stick with knockback enchantment
Disable the explosion of respawn blocks, e.g. beds or respawn anchors
carpet.rule.CCEUpdateSuppression.desc: By naming a shulker box with a specified name, an "ClassCastException"-based update suppressor can be created
carpet.rule.CCEUpdateSuppression.extra.0: If the value of the rule is false, the rule does not take effect
carpet.rule.CCEUpdateSuppression.extra.1: When the rule value is true, a shulker box named "更新抑制器" or "updateSuppression" can be used to make an update suppressor
carpet.rule.CCEUpdateSuppression.extra.2: If the rule value is a different string, the shulker box named that string can be used to make an update suppressor
carpet.rule.CCEUpdateSuppression.extra.3: Placing a shulker box for update suppression via dispenser removes its custom name
carpet.rule.openSeedPermission.desc: Allow players without permission to use /seed command
carpet.rule.openGameRulePermission.desc: Allow players without permission to use /gamerule command
carpet.rule.openVillagerInventory.desc: Allow to open villager inventory when sneaking
carpet.rule.commandXpTransfer.desc: Enable /xpTransfer to transfer experience between players
carpet.rule.commandSpectator.desc: Enable /spectator to switch between spectator and survival mode
carpet.rule.commandFinder.desc: Enable /finder command to search for blocks or items in certain ranges
carpet.rule.commandKillMe.desc: Enable /killme command to kill the player itself
carpet.rule.commandLocations.desc: Enable /locations command for location marker management
carpet.rule.healthNotFullCanEat.desc: You can eat food when full if your health is not full and saturation level less than 5
carpet.rule.canMineSpawner.desc: Make spawner mineable with silk touch tools
carpet.rule.fakePlayerSpawnNoKnockback.d: Remove the knockback, burning time and falling distance when fake players respawning
carpet.rule.canActivatesObserver.desc: Enable flint and steel used to directly activate observers
carpet.rule.disableWaterFreezes.desc: Disable water freezing in cold biomes
carpet.rule.fakePlayerActionKeepItem.des: When Fake Player perform item operations such as synthesis, trading, etc., they will keep at least one item in their inventory unless the item's maximum stack size is 1
carpet.rule.commandParticleLine.desc: Enable /particleLine command to draw a line connecting two points with particle effects
carpet.rule.disableMobPeacefulDespawn.de: Keep entities with "PersistenceRequired" tag (With naming, etc.) from despawning in peaceful mode
carpet.rule.climbingBoat.desc: Enable boat drove by player to climb up one block high
carpet.rule.reusableSmithingTemplate.des: Disable the consumption of smithing template when smithing
carpet.rule.reusableSmithingTemplate.ext: true: All smithing templates will not consumed
upgrade: Only netherite upgrade smithing template are preserved
carpet.rule.openTpPermission.desc: Allow players without permission to use /tp command
carpet.rule.softDeepslate.desc: Set the hardness of deepslate and its variants to be the same as stone or cobblestone
carpet.rule.softObsidian.desc: Set the hardness of obsidian to be the same as end stone
carpet.rule.softOres.desc: Set the hardness of ores to be the same as the corresponding stone, deepslate or end stone
carpet.rule.betterTotemOfUndying.desc: Undying Totem could function as long as it is in the inventory
carpet.rule.betterTotemOfUndying.extra.1: inventory_with_shulker_box: Function as if undying totem is in the inventory, including in shulker box
carpet.rule.betterTotemOfUndying.extra.2: inventory: Function as if undying totem is in the inventory, but excluding those in shulker box
carpet.rule.commandPlayerAction.desc: Enable /playerAction command to allow fake players to automatically perform some actions
carpet.rule.fakePlayerShulkerBoxItemHand: Allow fake player to directly access items from the Shulker Box
carpet.rule.customPiglinBarteringTime.de: Customize the time required for piglin bartering
Open the fake player crafting GUI directly by right-clicking the fake player with a workbench in mainhand, requiring the player to have the permission to execute the /playerAction command
carpet.rule.fakePlayerKeepInventory.desc: Keep inventories and experience when fake player dies
carpet.rule.fakePlayerKeepInventoryCondi: Controls conditional for fake player death drops
unconditional: Fake players never drop items
killed_by_player_or_the_void: Only keep inventory when killed by players or void
carpet.rule.commandCreeper.desc: Enable /creeper command to make a creeper explosion around the specified player. The explosion only damages entities, and cause no block damages
carpet.rule.commandRuleSearch.desc: Enable /ruleSearch to search for carpet rules with the specified string in the translated name
carpet.rule.superChargedCreeper.desc: Drop a head for each entity when killed by a charged creeper
carpet.rule.playerDropHead.desc: Player drops head when killed by a charged creeper
carpet.rule.beaconRangeExpand.desc: Extend range of beacon to specified distance
carpet.rule.beaconRangeExpand.extra.0: The value could be negative to shrink the range
carpet.rule.beaconWorldHeight.desc: Set the vertical range of beacon to the entire world height
carpet.rule.canHighlightBlockPos.desc: Add a button for highlight path point on the right of block position text
carpet.rule.commandPlayerManager.desc: Enable /playerManager command to manage fake players login
carpet.rule.blockDropsDirectlyEnterInven: Item dropping from mining will directly enter the player's inventory
If the value is custom, players can use the /orange command to enable the rules themselves
carpet.rule.turtleEggFastMine.desc: Player can mine multiple turtle eggs at once
carpet.rule.commandNavigate.desc: Enable /navigate command to guide players to a specific location
carpet.rule.playerDropsNotDespawning.des: Set the Age of player drops to -32768 to prevent them from despawning
carpet.rule.fakePlayerMaxItemOperationCo: Control the maximum number of times a fake player can perform operations such as synthesis trades in one game moment
carpet.rule.fakePlayerSpawnMemoryLeakFix: Fix memory leak issue caused by spawning fake player when fabric api is installed simultaneously
carpet.rule.commandMail.desc: Enable the /mail command to ship items to other players
carpet.rule.suppressionMismatchInDestroy: To prevent the warning "Mismatch in destroy block pos: {} {}" from being output in the log
carpet.rule.syncNavigateWaypoint.desc: When enabled, the waypoint position of the current navigator can be rendered on the client side
carpet.rule.shulkerBoxStackable.desc: Allow empty shulker box to stack up to 64
carpet.rule.shulkerBoxStackable.extra.0: This will not changing the behavior of hopper, dropper, crafter, and comparator
carpet.rule.shulkerBoxStackable.extra.1: When Lithium is installed at the same time, this rule is not compatible with features such as hopper counters
carpet.rule.maxBlockPlaceDistanceSyncCli: Whether it is allowed to change the distance of the client block placement
carpet.rule.limitPhantomSpawn.desc: The generation of Phantoms is affected by the spawn limit
Fix that the mining speed will not take effect immediately after switching tools
carpet.rule.forceRestock.desc: Always auto-populate hotbar item as much as possible
carpet.rule.autoSyncPlayerStatus.desc: The status of the inventory and surrounding blocks is automatically synchronized every 30 game tick
carpet.rule.recordPlayerCommand.desc: Outputs the commands executed by the player in the server console
carpet.rule.protectionEnchantmentCompati: Allow all protection enchantments to be compatible
Allow all damage enchantments to be compatible
carpet.rule.maxLinesPerPage.desc: Control the maximum number of lines allowed on each page of content
carpet.rule.villagerVoidTrading.desc: Prevent the transaction window from closing after moving out of the villager's interaction range to restore void trading as it was before 24w44a
carpet.rule.totemOfUndyingInvincibleTime: After activation, the Totem of Undying grants 2 seconds of Resistance V effect
carpet.rule.playerCommandOpenPlayerInven: Add the inventory subcommand to /player to open the player inventory interface
This rule is also the switch for the enderChest subcommand
carpet.rule.playerCommandTeleportFakePla: Add the teleport subcommand to /player to move fake player to your current location
carpet.rule.experienceOrbMerge.desc: Experience orb merging does not require equal value and ignores entity number
carpet.rule.quickShulker.desc: Allow direct opening of the shulker box in the inventory
carpet.rule.disableCreativeContainerDrop: Disables item drops from container block when broken in Creative mode
carpet.rule.disableFurnaceDropExperience: Prevent experience from dropping in a furnace
carpet.rule.setAnvilExperienceConsumptio: Set the maximum experience consumption level for a single operation of the anvil to a specified value
carpet.rule.playerCommandOpenPlayerInven: Control which player's inventory can be opened
fake_player: Allow opening fake player inventory
online_player: Allow opening any player inventory
all_player: Allow access to the inventory of any player, including offline player
non_whitelist: Allow opening offline player and fake player inventory. For whitelist player, OP permission is required to open the inventory
carpet.rule.playerManagerForceComment.de: Forcefully add comments when saving player data
carpet.rule.itemPickupRangeExpand.desc: Extend range of item pickup by specified distance
carpet.rule.itemPickupRangeExpandPlayerC: Allow players to decide for themselves whether to enable "itemPickupRangeExpand"
carpet.rule.message.CCEUpdateSuppression: You cannot open the shulkerbox for update surpression
carpet.rule.message.playerManagerForceCo: The "playerManagerForceComment" feature has been enabled, comments must be provided!
